        "body": "## Summary\n- assign known pricing to native Codex catalog rows instead of hardcoding zero cost for GPT-5 family models\n- fall back to local cost estimation when transcripts/runtime usage contain an explicit `$0` but the model has nonzero configured pricing\n- cover the regression with Codex catalog, runtime usage, and transcript aggregation tests\n\n## Notes\n- This targets the Codex/OpenAI cost regression where real token usage can be persisted with `usage.cost.total = 0`, causing dashboard and usage summaries to report false zero cost.\n- I could not run a full clean Vitest slice from a normal checkout in this runtime because the temporary export path kept losing repo test config files mid-run; the new tests were added alongside the fix, but broader CI should be treated as the real verifier here.",
